**Phase 2: Selection (1-2 months before)**
- Choose surgeon based on skill and trust
- Understand all costs
- Plan time off work (2-4 weeks depending on procedure)
- Arrange help for recovery
- Purchase recovery supplies

**Phase 3: Pre-Op (2-4 weeks before)**
- Pre-operative testing as required
- Stop medications as directed
- No alcohol
- Prepare recovery area at home
- Fill prescriptions in advance

**Phase 4: Recovery**
- Follow all post-op instructions exactly
- Wear compression garments as directed
- Rest appropriately
- Attend all follow-up appointments
- Be patient—final results take 3-6+ months

**Recovery Supplies:**
- Compression garments (surgeon-specified)
- Arnica gel/tablets (bruising)
- Scar treatment (silicone sheets/gel)
- Pillows for positioning
- Button-front clothing
